HEADWORD: Booking office
<hw>Book"ing of`fice</hw> <pr>(b⟦oocr⟧k"⟦icr⟧ng ⟦ocr⟧f`f⟦icr⟧s)</pr>.
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An office where passengers, baggage, etc., are
registered for conveyance, as by railway or steamship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An office where passage tickets are sold.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bookish</ent>⟦br⟧
